Digital Wallet Fields

The Digital Wallet object represents a digital payment method.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
NOTE Depending on your page layout and field-level security settings, some fields aren’t visible or editable.

This table lists the fields on the Digital Wallet object.

FIELD LABEL	DESCRIPTION
Account	The account of the customer who owns the digital wallet.
Audit Email	The email address of the digital wallet owner.
Comments	Comments about the digital wallet.
Company Name	The company name of the digital wallet owner.
Customer ID	The customer name of the digital wallet owner.
Gateway Token	The unique token ID generated by the payment gateway to represent the digital wallet payment method for future transactions. This version isn’t encrypted.
Gateway Token Details	Information about the gateway token.
Gateway Token Encrypted	The encrypted version of the unique token ID generated by the payment gateway to represent the digital wallet payment method for future transactions.
IP Address	The IP address of the digital wallet owner.
MAC Address	The MAC address of the user who initiated the payment.
Nickname	The nickname for the digital wallet.
Payment Gateway	The payment gateway used with transactions for the digital wallet.
Payment Method Address	Part of the address for the payment method.
Phone	The phone number of the digital wallet owner.
Processing Mode	

Indicates whether the digital wallet is used for transactions made inside or outside the payment platform.

Possible values are:

External—Transaction occurred outside of the Salesforce payment platform.
Salesforce—Salesforce made and recorded an external call to the payment platform.

Registered Email	The email address of the digital wallet owner.
